  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0cm 5.75pt 0cm 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Small green and brown skinned rodents. The Jintus ev=
olved
  as a species off shoot from the same ancestors as the Ugnari. <br>
  <br>
  The Jintus are often getting themselves in some form of conflict, however=
 they
  are not very enthusiastic about actually fighting. They will often draw in
  their allies to fight their own battles, using their chosen friends as the
  intimidation factor in any war. <br>
  <br>
  The Jintus favour races they consider to be strong and able to win wars f=
or
  them. <br>
  <br>
  Living and hunting in packs, pack feuds and wars are common. Hunting
  Terrellions is a sport they enjoy and will often lose their life to as the
  Terrellion is three times the size of the Jintus in body weight. <br>
  <br>
  Jintus inhabit caves and other natural or intelligently made shelters of =
ice
  worlds. Not very good engineers they will kill or drive out occupants of
  these potential habitats to find warm homes.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Jintus preferred weapon is the Rail Gun and they=
 focus
  on Speed and Agility with Energy Research.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>In game term=
s this
  race is almost a minor race, the AI will not do very well with this race.
  They will cause conflict in the Galaxy as they try to make alliances and
  provoke wars. For the player it is a challenging race to play as it has v=
ery
  few advantages and difficult win conditions to achieve.<o:p></o:p></i></p>
